change dynamically as tasks are added, edited, or removed, and the totals
should not be limited to saved tasks, but reflect only what's currently
shown on the page.

The rest of the application behaviour should remain exactly the same.
</show-hour-totals>



<zero-hours-actual-ok>
When a task's actual hours is set to zero and saved, that zero should 
be saved to the REST API server in the normal way and also preserved in
the task.  Any tasks with zero actual hours should be considered complete
and not highlighted.  Tasks in days that have zero in actual hours, if
there are no tasks with blank actual hours, should NOT be highlighted.
Any day and task that has blank Acutal hours should be highlighted as
before.

The rest of the application behaviour should remain exactly the same.

# It said that this is already done

Right now, when I put a zero into the Actual hours field, it isn't
saved or persisted.  When I put either 0 or 0.0 in the Actual field,
and click Save, it just disappears, and the task and day remain
highlighted.  Please fix this.

